    "description": "Infomart Corporation operates a business-to-business (BtoB) electronic commerce platform in Japan. The company operates in BtoB-PF FOOD business and BtoB-PFES business segments. The company offers BtoB Platform Invoices that digitalize both invoice receipt and issuance.; BtoB Platform Ordering for digitize everything from order placement to invoicing; BtoB platform TRADE to manage quotation, ordering, receiving, delivery, inspection, and invoicing operations digitally; BtoB Platform Ordering Lite for managing Order information from faxes, telephone calls, emails, and on the cloud; BtoB Platform Contract, a secure electronic contract service; TANOMU, a wholesale ordering system; and BP Storage for digitizing everything from invoice receipt and issuance, expense reimbursement, document storage, and carbon dioxide emission measurement. It also provides BtoB Platform Negotiations for Matching sellers, food wholesalers, restaurants, and other businesses with buyers; V-Manage to digitally manage store operations and management task; AI-OCR (invox), an AI OCR processes and digitizes faxes, emails, and PDF purchase orders; BP Workflow to digitizing internal approval and application procedures; electronic bill early payment that convert pending invoices into cash; BtoB Platform Quotation which centralized and digitized receipt and quotation; BtoB platform industry channel, an industry information portal site that streamlines sales and planning operations; Menu Plus, digitize your restaurant's menu management; Kauri Kessai, streamline processes, such as credit checks for business partners, payment collection, and payment reconciliation; BtoB platform order placement; and BtoB eSmart, a commercial food ingredients, supplies, and materials site. Infomart Corporation was incorporated in 1998 and is headquartered in Minato, Japan."
